{
  "id": "2021-04-08_screen_english",
  "date": "2021-04-08",
  "corner": "screen_english",
  "corner_label": "Screen English",
  "title": "",
  "movie": "밀리언 달러 트러블",
  "duration_sec": 747.62,
  "audio_url": "https://rtyzdyyfahddqshgyjvn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/gmp-audio/2021-04-08_screen_english.mp3",
  "script": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 2.3,
      "text": "굿모닝 그리스"
    },
    {
      "start": 2.3,
      "end": 3.78,
      "text": "굿모닝 조정현씨"
    },
    {
      "start": 3.78,
      "end": 7.78,
      "text": "언제 들어도 반가운 그리스씨 오셨습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 8.42,
      "end": 10.36,
      "text": "사실 apparently 할머니가요"
    },
    {
      "start": 10.36,
      "end": 12.9,
      "text": "She was a very rich lady"
    },
    {
      "start": 12.9,
      "end": 13.98,
      "text": "Super rich"
    },
    {
      "start": 13.98,
      "end": 15.14,
      "text": "Ultra wealthy"
    },
    {
      "start": 15.14,
      "end": 18.3,
      "text": "완전 super rich하고 ultra wealthy"
    },
    {
      "start": 18.3,
      "end": 19.8,
      "text": "이 표현도 아주 마음에 드네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 19.9,
      "end": 20.5,
      "text": "You like that?"
    },
    {
      "start": 20.62,
      "end": 20.88,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 20.98,
      "end": 21.7,
      "text": "Ultra wealthy"
    },
    {
      "start": 21.7,
      "end": 30.42,
      "text": "그리고 이렇게 엄청난 유산을 자기가 키우던 강아지나 아니면 고양이한테 남기는 주인들이 종종 있잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 30.88,
      "end": 33.52,
      "text": "I've often heard about it on world news."
    },
    {
      "start": 33.88,
      "end": 34.14,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 34.14,
      "end": 35.52,
      "text": "진짜 실제로 있더라고요."
    },
    {
      "start": 35.52,
      "end": 37.14,
      "text": "This actually happens."
    },
    {
      "start": 37.74,
      "end": 42.68,
      "text": "In 2018, the world's richest dog became the richest dog."
    },
    {
      "start": 43.1,
      "end": 44.38,
      "text": "His name was Gunther."
    },
    {
      "start": 44.6,
      "end": 45.92,
      "text": "He was a German shepherd."
    },
    {
      "start": 46.08,
      "end": 46.2,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 46.72,
      "end": 54.78,
      "text": "And his owner gave him an inheritance of 65 million dollars when she died."
    },
    {
      "start": 55.0,
      "end": 56.44,
      "text": "65 million."
    },
    {
      "start": 56.64,
      "end": 59.04,
      "text": "6,500만 달러면 환율이 어떻게 되죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 59.1,
      "end": 61.66,
      "text": "환산하면 한 740억?"
    },
    {
      "start": 62.14,
      "end": 63.02,
      "text": "Oh, yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 63.58,
      "end": 64.26,
      "text": "환율까지."
    },
    {
      "start": 64.26,
      "end": 65.7,
      "text": "어머니 복잡한데."
    },
    {
      "start": 66.48,
      "end": 66.54,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 66.54,
      "end": 67.66,
      "text": "거기쯤."
    },
    {
      "start": 67.76,
      "end": 67.94,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 68.36,
      "end": 70.08,
      "text": "740억을 상속을 받았네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 70.58,
      "end": 76.3,
      "text": "And his owner was the late German countess, Carlato Liebestain."
    },
    {
      "start": 76.4,
      "end": 77.8,
      "text": "She died in 1992."
    },
    {
      "start": 78.12,
      "end": 81.78,
      "text": "Anyway, a really rich German lady left him a ton of money."
    },
    {
      "start": 82.44,
      "end": 86.46,
      "text": "And of course, dogs have trouble managing money because they're dogs."
    },
    {
      "start": 86.46,
      "end": 90.08,
      "text": "So he had people around him to manage his money."
    },
    {
      "start": 90.08,
      "end": 96.42,
      "text": "And they turned that 65 million dollars into 375 million dollars."
    },
    {
      "start": 96.9,
      "end": 97.98,
      "text": "머리가 폭발할 것 같아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 98.14,
      "end": 99.22,
      "text": "That's a lot of money."
    },
    {
      "start": 99.48,
      "end": 99.62,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 99.78,
      "end": 106.66,
      "text": "3억 7,500만 달러라고 했으니까 환산하면 4,300억 원으로 재산을 불렸다고 합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 106.66,
      "end": 112.76,
      "text": "Anyway, Gunther the dog had a son, Gunther the 4th."
    },
    {
      "start": 112.76,
      "end": 118.32,
      "text": "So that 375 million dollars was passed onto the son, a dog."
    },
    {
      "start": 118.9,
      "end": 122.58,
      "text": "And now his handlers are managing that money."
    },
    {
      "start": 122.58,
      "end": 127.12,
      "text": "And they're buying property, mansions, villas, all over the world."
    },
    {
      "start": 127.56,
      "end": 131.02,
      "text": "And he's considered the world's richest dog, Gunther the 4th."
    },
    {
      "start": 131.6,
      "end": 132.58,
      "text": "Jealous of a dog."
    },
    {
      "start": 133.08,
      "end": 133.44,
      "text": "정말."
    },
    {
      "start": 134.28,
      "end": 135.98,
      "text": "정말 부럽습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 136.02,
      "end": 136.76,
      "text": "They have the life."
    },
    {
      "start": 136.84,
      "end": 137.34,
      "text": "그러네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 137.58,
      "end": 138.7,
      "text": "그때 그 말."
    },
    {
      "start": 138.86,
      "end": 141.42,
      "text": "딱 배운 표현을 여기에다가 써먹으면 되겠네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 141.54,
      "end": 141.82,
      "text": "아, 네."
    },
    {
      "start": 142.18,
      "end": 143.52,
      "text": "와, 정말 부럽습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 143.64,
      "end": 145.96,
      "text": "부러면 지는 거라고 하지만 저는 그래도 부럽네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 146.74,
      "end": 148.2,
      "text": "아, 저 이게 키울게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 148.34,
      "end": 148.98,
      "text": "아, 진짜?"
    },
    {
      "start": 149.26,
      "end": 150.02,
      "text": "그러고 싶습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 150.08,
      "end": 150.76,
      "text": "입양하고 싶어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 150.76,
      "end": 151.04,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 151.42,
      "end": 152.02,
      "text": "아, 참."
    },
    {
      "start": 152.02,
      "end": 155.86,
      "text": "그래도 우리가 sometimes we say, dogs are better than people."
    },
    {
      "start": 156.14,
      "end": 156.64,
      "text": "그죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 156.98,
      "end": 160.52,
      "text": "그래서 이런 상황이 종종 가능하지 않나 싶기도 하네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 160.64,
      "end": 161.76,
      "text": "They don't care about wealth."
    },
    {
      "start": 162.16,
      "end": 163.7,
      "text": "They just need love and food."
    },
    {
      "start": 163.78,
      "end": 164.1,
      "text": "그죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 164.12,
      "end": 164.64,
      "text": "and intention."
    },
    {
      "start": 164.92,
      "end": 165.12,
      "text": "예."
    },
    {
      "start": 165.54,
      "end": 167.1,
      "text": "자, 오늘 내용 먼저 듣고 오겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 167.98,
      "end": 169.66,
      "text": "You're an outside dog?"
    },
    {
      "start": 169.8,
      "end": 170.66,
      "text": "Don't you label me."
    },
    {
      "start": 171.28,
      "end": 172.06,
      "text": "It's cool."
    },
    {
      "start": 172.3,
      "end": 173.14,
      "text": "Totally cool."
    },
    {
      "start": 173.84,
      "end": 175.54,
      "text": "This is not ideal."
    },
    {
      "start": 175.88,
      "end": 180.47,
      "text": "I haven't had my teeth brushed and there are an alarming lack of pillows."
    },
    {
      "start": 180.47,
      "end": 183.39,
      "text": "I don't suppose you have something like a warm blanket?"
    },
    {
      "start": 184.31,
      "end": 185.39,
      "text": "Perhaps cashmere?"
    },
    {
      "start": 186.2,
      "end": 186.7,
      "text": "Comfy?"
    },
    {
      "start": 187.28,
      "end": 187.86,
      "text": "Why, yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 188.4,
      "end": 189.24,
      "text": "Yes, I am."
    },
    {
      "start": 189.88,
      "end": 190.68,
      "text": "I don't snuggle."
    },
    {
      "start": 190.68,
      "end": 197.54,
      "text": "Yeah, finally, Trouble realized the fact that Rousey was a stray dog."
    },
    {
      "start": 197.76,
      "end": 198.94,
      "text": "Yeah, no home."
    },
    {
      "start": 199.12,
      "end": 200.22,
      "text": "No current home."
    },
    {
      "start": 200.22,
      "end": 204.28,
      "text": "그래서 그 place where Rousey brought him was not a house."
    },
    {
      "start": 204.38,
      "end": 204.7,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "start": 204.88,
      "end": 205.2,
      "text": "At all."
    },
    {
      "start": 205.7,
      "end": 206.1,
      "text": "Outdoors."
    },
    {
      "start": 206.52,
      "end": 208.5,
      "text": "완전 just a bare ground."
    },
    {
      "start": 208.7,
      "end": 209.08,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 209.48,
      "end": 213.72,
      "text": "완전 맨땅에서 그냥 잠을 자야 하는 상황에 놓여가지고"
    },
    {
      "start": 213.72,
      "end": 217.4,
      "text": "트러블이 적자니 당황한 그런 상황이었습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 217.4,
      "end": 219.24,
      "text": "He's out in the real world now."
    },
    {
      "start": 219.3,
      "end": 219.56,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 219.64,
      "end": 223.32,
      "text": "He has to face harsh weather and lack of food."
    },
    {
      "start": 223.46,
      "end": 225.5,
      "text": "He has to survive himself."
    },
    {
      "start": 226.4,
      "end": 228.7,
      "text": "A good thing he has this big tough dog next to him."
    },
    {
      "start": 228.88,
      "end": 230.24,
      "text": "They were not friends at first."
    },
    {
      "start": 230.3,
      "end": 232.18,
      "text": "But now he's helping him."
    },
    {
      "start": 232.18,
      "end": 239.18,
      "text": "그런데 Rousey의 표정이 뭔가 좀 비하인드 스토리가 분명히 있을 것 같다라는 생각을 하게 하더라고요."
    },
    {
      "start": 239.3,
      "end": 240.0,
      "text": "눈빛 받죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 240.04,
      "end": 240.28,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 240.48,
      "end": 243.32,
      "text": "That, he has a sad look behind his eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 243.44,
      "end": 246.16,
      "text": "You can tell that he has some kind of dark past."
    },
    {
      "start": 246.2,
      "end": 246.64,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 246.64,
      "end": 249.18,
      "text": "아, 자, 차차 알게 되겠죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 249.62,
      "end": 250.9,
      "text": "먼저 표현들 알려주세요."
    },
    {
      "start": 251.74,
      "end": 253.1,
      "text": "Outside dog."
    },
    {
      "start": 253.3,
      "end": 257.38,
      "text": "Outside dog 하면 떠돌이 개라고 해석할 수 있어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 257.92,
      "end": 260.52,
      "text": "뭐 stray dog라는 표현도 가능하겠죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 260.52,
      "end": 260.76,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 260.92,
      "end": 268.06,
      "text": "Stray dog이랑 다른 게, I could 키우고 있더라도, I could have an outside dog or an indoor dog."
    },
    {
      "start": 268.18,
      "end": 271.6,
      "text": "Some people only keep their dogs outside and they have a dog house."
    },
    {
      "start": 271.82,
      "end": 274.36,
      "text": "And some people like to keep their dogs inside."
    },
    {
      "start": 274.52,
      "end": 276.54,
      "text": "Some people keep them inside and outside."
    },
    {
      "start": 276.64,
      "end": 277.88,
      "text": "It depends on the owner."
    },
    {
      "start": 278.1,
      "end": 278.42,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 278.66,
      "end": 279.88,
      "text": "Outdoor dog 그런 말이에요."
    },
    {
      "start": 279.98,
      "end": 280.52,
      "text": "아, 그래요."
    },
    {
      "start": 280.62,
      "end": 285.28,
      "text": "떠돌이 개뿐 아니라 집에서 주인이 직접 키우고 있더라도,"
    },
    {
      "start": 285.64,
      "end": 291.02,
      "text": "바깥에 집을 만들어주고, 바깥에서 지내고 있는 강아지들을 outside dog라고도 할 수 있다."
    },
    {
      "start": 291.02,
      "end": 292.7,
      "text": "라는 친절한 설명을 해주셨습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 292.7,
      "end": 294.18,
      "text": "따돌리는 개는 그냥 stray."
    },
    {
      "start": 294.36,
      "end": 294.64,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 294.64,
      "end": 295.22,
      "text": "Stray dog."
    },
    {
      "start": 295.26,
      "end": 295.8,
      "text": "Stray dog."
    },
    {
      "start": 295.84,
      "end": 296.58,
      "text": "Homeless dog."
    },
    {
      "start": 297.94,
      "end": 299.18,
      "text": "Don't you label me?"
    },
    {
      "start": 299.36,
      "end": 302.6,
      "text": "Oh, 이거 label이라는 단어는 우리가 3월 영화에서도 배웠잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 302.74,
      "end": 303.5,
      "text": "라벨, 라벨."
    },
    {
      "start": 304.04,
      "end": 304.56,
      "text": "Label."
    },
    {
      "start": 304.56,
      "end": 306.28,
      "text": "네, 여기서도 또 들렸네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 306.38,
      "end": 307.34,
      "text": "여기가 좀 다른 말이네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 307.34,
      "end": 307.56,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 307.86,
      "end": 309.28,
      "text": "Don't you label me?"
    },
    {
      "start": 309.4,
      "end": 311.4,
      "text": "라고 했으니까, 날 그렇게 부르지 마."
    },
    {
      "start": 311.96,
      "end": 314.06,
      "text": "나한테 그렇게 꼬리표 붙이지 마."
    },
    {
      "start": 314.14,
      "end": 314.96,
      "text": "라는 겁니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 315.2,
      "end": 316.76,
      "text": "Don't put me inside a box."
    },
    {
      "start": 317.02,
      "end": 318.06,
      "text": "Don't call me that."
    },
    {
      "start": 318.06,
      "end": 319.3,
      "text": "아, 그 표현도 좋으네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 319.52,
      "end": 321.28,
      "text": "Don't put me inside the box."
    },
    {
      "start": 321.56,
      "end": 321.9,
      "text": "틀 안에."
    },
    {
      "start": 322.14,
      "end": 323.66,
      "text": "나를 틀 안에 가두지 마."
    },
    {
      "start": 323.76,
      "end": 323.94,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 324.08,
      "end": 325.22,
      "text": "좋은 표현입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 325.3,
      "end": 325.78,
      "text": "많이 써요."
    },
    {
      "start": 325.84,
      "end": 326.02,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 326.12,
      "end": 326.82,
      "text": "Don't label me."
    },
    {
      "start": 327.98,
      "end": 329.78,
      "text": "I don't snuggle."
    },
    {
      "start": 330.9,
      "end": 332.8,
      "text": "Snuggle이라는 철자 알려드리면,"
    },
    {
      "start": 332.96,
      "end": 336.4,
      "text": "S-N-U-G-G-L-E라는 철자인데,"
    },
    {
      "start": 336.88,
      "end": 341.14,
      "text": "뭐, 껴안다, 파고 들다, 아니면 들러붙다, 라는 의미잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 341.46,
      "end": 342.42,
      "text": "그래서 I don't snuggle."
    },
    {
      "start": 342.6,
      "end": 344.3,
      "text": "나는 들러붙는 거 싫어해."
    },
    {
      "start": 344.38,
      "end": 345.9,
      "text": "나는 안 들러붙거든."
    },
    {
      "start": 346.14,
      "end": 347.0,
      "text": "이라는 의미입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 347.0,
      "end": 348.18,
      "text": "스킨십 싫어하거든."
    },
    {
      "start": 348.42,
      "end": 348.48,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 348.58,
      "end": 349.24,
